I really had a hard time installing RISA 3D. But after a few trials I did get it to work. In case some people are wondering how, try this:

1. Run Setup
2. After accepting the terms of the license agreement the "Setup Type" dialouge box will appear. Select "Custom" then click Next.
3. Change the folder where you want to install (e.g. C:\Program Files\RISA). It might be necessary to create a folder first where you want RISA to be installed. Click Next.
4. On the "Select Features" dialouge box make sure all the features are checked. Click Next.
5. Click Next on the "Select Program Folder" dialouge box then click Install.
6. When a dialouge box saying "Please remove all USB Sentinel SuperPro keys from your system before continuing." appears, just click OK.
7. Click Finish after installing
8. Copy the crack named "RISA3d55" to the installation folder (e.g. C:\Program Files\RISA). The crack is located at the "RISA_TECHNOLOGIES_RISA_3D_V5[1].5-LND" folder.
9. Launch the crack that you just copied. 
10. Click Restore. It should say on the status textbox "file sucessfuly restored".
11. Click Patch. It should say on the status textbox "file sucessfuly patched".
12. Launch the program "risa3dw".
